    "body": "The `gui-tk.py` example is working for me in the notebook. Note that you need to start the event loop in a special way to integrate with IPython. The example has this code at the bottom:\n\n```\ntry:\n    from IPython.lib.inputhook import enable_tk; enable_tk(root)\nexcept ImportError:\n    root.mainloop()\n```\n\nClosing for now, we can reopen if you think there's a problem.\n"
